text: Ellen Rose Noble (born December 3, 1995) is an American professional racing cyclist, who currently rides for Trek Factory Racing in cyclo-cross and mountain bike racing. In 2019, Noble was named as part of UCI Women's Team for the women's road cycling season. == Major results == === 2018 === : 2nd United States National Cyclo-cross Championships : 3rd United States National Cyclo- Cross Championships === 2017 === : 2nd UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships :1st U23 United States National Cyclo-cross Championships === 2016 === :1st U23 United States National Cyclo-cross Championships ==References== ==External links== * Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:American female cyclists Category:People from Kennebunkport, Maine
